	(text "- LowChan and HighChan are gpio outputs,\n   controlling the low and high current load \n   drivers respectively\n- All MCU pins are connected via buses, which\n   connect to other hierarchical sheets\n- GPIO[0..4] are to be used as needed later.\n   Connector is TBD. The first 3 are capable\n   of GPIO or PWM output.\n- Channel buttons (used for debugging) are\n   connected with RC low pass filter for button\n   debouncing. Time constant is 10ms. Look at\n   TI app note for info.\n- No external pulldown on the channel inputs\n   because the load driver chip comes with them\n   internally."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 102.87 120.65 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "bd958e98-45b5-4b55-8905-e69467b34b6a")
	)
